<div class="ttlwrapper">
<div class="ttlbgwide">
<div class="ttlred" id="ttlpos">Overview</div></div>
<p>The Office of Fair Housing and Equal Opportunity (FHEO) administers and enforces <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120402122117/http://www.hud.gov/offices/fheo/FHLaws/index.cfm">federal laws</a> and establishes policies that make sure all Americans have equal access to the housing of their choice. <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120402122117/http://www.hud.gov/offices/fheo/aboutfheo/aboutfheo.cfm">Learn more about FHEO</a>, or contact the Housing Discrimination Hotline by <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120402122117/mailto:fheo_webmanager@hud.gov">email</a>, or at <b>1-800-669-9777 (Voice)</b> | 1<b>-800-927-9275 (TTY).</b></p>
<table style="width: 100%">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="width: 239px"><b><img alt="No Vacancy Sign" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20120402122117im_/http://portal.hud.gov/hudportal/images/hudimg?id=NOVACANCY.JPG" style="float: left; width: 217px; height: 156px"/></b></td>
<td>
<div class="genlink">
<ul>
<li><b>&nbsp;<a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120402122117/http://portal.hud.gov/hudportal/HUD/program_offices/fair_housing_equal_opp/enforcement">HUD Discrimination Charges</a></b></li>
<li><b>&nbsp;<a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120402122117/http://portal.hud.gov/hudportal/HUD?mode=disppage&amp;id=11DECREESCONCILIATION">Consent Decrees/Conciliation Agreements </a></b></li>
<li><b>&nbsp;<a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120402122117/http://portal.hud.gov/hudportal/HUD?mode=disppage&amp;id=11SECADMINLAWJUDGE">Secretarial and Administrative Law Judge Orders</a></b></li></ul></div>
